        public void stayLoggedIn(boolean value)
        By default, the MoneytreeLink client will automatically refresh the authentication token when expired. Passing false will disable this automatically refresh, and users will need to re-authenticate every time the token expires.

      • openVault

        public void openVault(int requestCode,
                      @NonNull
                      LinkRequestContext requestContext)
        Open the vault. The user needs to log in to the Moneytree beforehand. If not the authorization flow will launch first.

        onActivityResult for either the Fragment or Activity passed to the LinkRequestContext.Builder will be invoked once the vault has closed with result code result code RESULT_CODE_VAULT_CLOSED and the given requestCode in .

        Parameters:
        requestCode - Request code if for the Vault close callback.
        requestContext - A Link request context that has all request options.
        Since:
        5.3.1

      • getToken

        public void getToken(@NonNull
                     Authorization.OnCompletionListener listener)
        Get a valid token. Only supported when the authentiction type is PKCE.

        If the token has not yet expired and is still valid the completionHandler is invoked with a valid token; otherwise, the refresh token is used to fetch a new valid token before invoking the completion handler with the update token. When stayLoggedIn(boolean) is set to false, the user will be required to complete the authorization flow again.

        We recommend using the getToken(Authorization.OnCompletionListener, Activity) instead.

        Specified by:
        getToken in interface com.getmoneytree.auth.OAuthCredentialProvider
        Parameters:
        listener - A completion handler for when the token is available.
        Since:
        1.0.0

      • getToken

        public void getToken(@NonNull
                     Authorization.OnCompletionListener listener,
                     @Nullable
                     android.app.Activity activity)
        Get a valid token. Only supported when the authentication type is PKCE.

        If the token has not yet expired and is still valid the completionHandler is invoked with a valid token; otherwise, the refresh token is used to fetch a new valid token before invoking the completion handler with the update token. When stayLoggedIn(boolean) is set to false, the user will be required to complete the authorization flow again.

        Parameters:
        listener - A completion handler for when the token is available.
        activity - An activity that opens authorization screen when needed.
        Since:
        1.0.0

      • registerDeviceTokenFrom

        public void registerDeviceTokenFrom(@Nullable
                                    android.app.Activity activity,
                                    @NonNull
                                    java.lang.String deviceToken,
                                    @Nullable
                                    Api.OnCompletionListener listener)
        Register device token. This method requires an access token. See also authorizeFrom(Activity, MoneytreeAuthOptions).

        Note when using Issho Tsucho the registered device token will be unregistered when the user logs out of Issho Tsucho.

        Parameters:

        listener - a completion handler that runs after an attempt to register the token
        Since:
        2.0.0
